            <div class="everyonelovesstackoverflow" id="adzerk679436254">
            </div>

            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
lvm (logical volume manager) is a software that allows disk partitionning by hiding the physical limitations of the underlying disks.  It can make logical partitions from separate physical partitions even on separate disks, hide mirroring, allow increasing the size of a logical volume while used and ...                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/lvm/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/lvm/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/lvm/synonyms">synonyms</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

